{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chia seeds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and mix with 6 Tbsp water then set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh in cauliflower then steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Remove Varoma dish and discard cooking water.","Place cooked cauliflower, reserved chia mixture, salt, pepper, garlic, curry paste, tomatoes, onions, herbs and black beans in mixing bowl. Blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b> while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Place a shallow bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in polenta then set aside. Roll 1½ Tbsp of mixture into 30 balls then roll in polenta to coat. Transfer to a baking tray and refrigerate for 30 minutes.","Towards the end of chilling time, heat 2 Tbsp sunflower oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Fry balls in batches for 5 minutes until golden brown, turning occasionally, adding up to 2 Tbsp extra oil as necessary. Serve warm or cold (see tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 Tbsp chia seeds","500 g water, plus 6 Tbsp water","400 g cauliflower, in pieces (3-4 cm)","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground pepper","1 garlic clove","2 Tbsp red curry paste (30 g)","95 g tomatoes, quartered","60 g onions, quartered","10 g mixed fresh herbs, leaves only, to taste (e.g parsley, coriander)","240 g black beans, tinned, drained (1 x 400 g tin)","100 g polenta, for coating","4 Tbsp sunflower oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r145630","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZmIAKpsAaOM\/XZVRF7d-6SI\/AAAAAAAAdJ0\/CbICOP1edL4NHwC1Z9Ofro-wsHGJPUJEQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ejgevNbuGYNfPRZ4.png","title":"Cauliflower and Black Bean Balls","publishedAt":"2017-04-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"40.6 g","fat":"46.3 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"142.1 g","calories":"4803 kJ \/ 1148 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow bowl or dish, baking tray, frying pan, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["These bean balls are so versatile; serve with salad and your favourite dressing, with a ragu sauce with rice or eat them as a snack on the go!<br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 10m","30 pieces"]}